   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRR &amp; RBP: Assam &amp; Pune</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Disaster Risk Reduction and Resilience Building Program in rural and urban sectors of Assam and Pune in India aligns with Climate Justice pillar and focuses on disaster risk reduction in the north east state of Assa, disaster risk reduction in urban slums of cities if such as Mumbai (with a special focus on marginal communities), and national level work that supports local humanitarian leaders (mainly women and girls).   The initiative also entails state and national advocacy on disaster risk reduction and inter agency coordination.</narrative>
